Plastic pollution treaty talks open with 'global crisis' warning
description: Delegates from over 180 countries began final talks Tuesday in Geneva to craft a global treaty on plastic pollution, amid mounting pressure to curb a crisis threatening ecosystems, health, and the planet. 'The urgency is real, the evidence is clear – and the responsibility is on us,' said Ecuadorian diplomat Luis Vayas Valdivieso.

headline: The calculated return of Kamala Harris after defeat and months of silence
description: The former vice president of the United States has announced the release of a memoir, '107 Days,' out September 23, revealing the behind-the-scenes from her presidential campaign. Harris, who appeared Thursday on Stephen Colbert's 'The Late Show' on CBS, has remained vague, however, about the future of her political involvement.

headline: A Hiroshima survivor breaks decades of silence: 'Speaking about it could be seen as shameful, for the person or their family'
description: Toshiko Tanaka, now 86, kept silent about her trauma for 65 years. Today, she travels the world to campaign against nuclear weapons and is scheduled to speak on Japanese television during the commemoration of the August 6, 1945 bombing.

description: 'Of Volcanoes and Men' (2/6). French photographer Marguerite Bornhauser ventured onto the Colombian volcano, at an altitude of over 5,000 meters, in the summer of 2024. headline: The sci-fi classic that shaped Elon Musk's worldview
description: 'Musk Fictions' (1/6). The billionaire has long drawn inspiration from 'The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy', Douglas Adams's cult sci-fi series about artificial intelligence, towels and the destruction of Earth.
